BAUCHI – A House of Assembly aspirant for the Azare/Madangala State Constituency of Bauchi State on the platform of the Social Democratic Party (SDP), Honourable Ahmad Shehu Na-Allah, has promised to offer quality representation to his constituency if elected. Hon Na-Allah spoke to newsmen on Friday at the SDP Secretariat after submitting his party’s expression of interest and nomination form for the State House of Assembly election. Na-Allah, who disclosed that he was in the race to contribute his quota to the development of the state as well as provide positive change to his constituency, adding that he has the right expertise and credentials to represent the constituency. -Advertisement- Unfolding his agenda, Na-Allah stated that he will focus on youth empowerment, educational development and youth inclusiveness and participation in politics. He however urged the electorates to elect competent and credible persons who will bring positive change to the constituency. Na- Allah said his party SDP has been repositioned in the state to dislodge the ruling party , alleging that the two major parties, PDP and APC have failed in fulfilling their campaign promises in 2015 and 2019. “I want to contribute my quota to my constituency and the country, my focus is the empowerment of the youths, education and youth inclusiveness and participation in politics. People are tired of the empty promises of the PDP and APC as they have not delivered on their promises, the PDP and APC have failed on their promises,” he said